{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_oliver_ver01/data/sn83045462/00280600568/1930102701/0126.xml":{"full_text":"HOME REPAIR JOBS\nURGED TO ME\nPainting* and Other improve\nments Advocated by Woods\nto Help Unemployed.\nBy the Associated Press.\nNEW YORK, October 27.\u2014Spruce up\nand create jobs, a request comes from\nCol. Arthur Woods, chairman of Presi\ndent Hoover\u2019s Emergency Committee.\nIn a radio cast address last night\nCol. Woods appealed to individual\nAmerican families to provide work.\n\u201cLet us all spruce up our homes,\" he\n\u25a0aid. \u201cMake the little repairs that are\nneeded, do that little job of painting\nthat we thought about so long, fix up\nthe odd comers of the yard, replace the\nworn-out or broken parts that halt the\nsmooth running of the household.\nNeeded Improvements Cited.\n\u201cLet us do the same thing in our\ncommunities. We can give work to\nhundreds of thousands by improving\nshabby playgrounds, unsightly vacant\nlots, dirty streets and by cleaning up\nall those community black spots that\nhave annoyed us as conscientious cit\nizens so long.\"\nCol. Woods announced that three ad\nditional leaders in their fields had ac\ncepted places on his committee. They\nare Dr. Lillian Moller Gilbreth, doctor\nof engineering and consulting engineer\non management, who will direct the\nwomen\u2019s division of the committee:\nPorter Lee, president in 1929 of the Na\ntional Conference of Social Work, who\nwill gather Information on the welfare\naspects of unemployment, and Bryce\nStewart, employment statistician.\nWall Street Giving Aid.\nSeward Prosser, New York banker,\nhas announced that many of the\nyounger executives in Wall Street are\nrallying to the support of his emergency\ncommittee, formed to raise $150,000 a\nweek to provide jobs for unemployed\nheads of families.\nJohn D. Rockefeller, jr., has an\nhounced plans for the construction this\nWinter of 14 double houses on his Po\n\u2022antlco Hills estate, at Tarrytown. N.\nY., to be rented to his employes at a\nnominal rental. They will cost $15,000\nand upward each.\nDR. SURFACE PREDICTS\nHARD TIMES CONTROL\nBusiness Men and Economists Will\nCombine Efforts Against\nDepression, He Says.\nDr. Prank Surface, assistant\ndirector of the of Foreign and\nDomestic Commerce, predicted last\nnight that possible future business de\npressions could h* made susceptible to\ncontrol by \u201cthe combined efforts of\nthousands of business men and\neconomists.\u201d\nIn a radio address over the Columbia\nBroadcasting System, Dr. Surface said\nthat the chance of such a control\nsystem developing depended upon \u201cpro\nper support and co-operation from the\nbusiness public.\u201d\n\u201cWhen business has passed into a\nperiod of depression there seems to be\nlittle that can be done byway of defi\nnite control.\u201d he said. \u201cPrevention,\nnot cure, is the modem trend in medi\ncine and so it must be with these\neconomic disorders.\u201d\nOverproduction, principally of raw\nmaterials, was described by Dr. Surface\nas a mime cause of difficulty. Improved\nreporting of facts and better adjustment\nof production to demand were suggested\n\u2022s methods of attacking the problem.\nPresent conditions, he said, rep re\ngen ted \u201cthe greatest challenge to con\nstructive business thinking the world\nhas yet witnessed.\u201d\nBpanisb Census to Be Taken.\nMADRID, October 27 OP).\u2014A census\nof Spain\u2019s population at home and In\nher overseas possessions was ordered by\na royal decree published yesterday. The\nenumeration will be made as of next\nJanuary 1.\nSPECIAL NOTICES.\nATJ.nen van lw\u00a3 MOTOR VAN Wt\nnovtlt anywhere. \"Pool\u2019' vans for *h la\nment. of small lots to and from New York.\nSECURITY STORAGE COMPANY. 1140 Plf\nteenth street. Decatur 04*s.\nON AND APTEFfTHIS DATE I WEL NOT\nbe responsible for any debts contracted by\nany other than myself. W. A. SHANNON.\n<715 2nd st. n.w. 2T\nI WILL NOT BE RESPONSIBLE FOR ANY\ndebts other than thoae